  "explanation": "The defendant is convicted of embezzling $25,000 from their employer, a serious breach of fiduciary duty. However, in determining the sentence, I must weigh several mitigating factors. The defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made partial restitution, demonstrating remorse and a genuine effort to make amends. The spectator's outburst suggesting a 10-year sentence is entirely disproportionate to a first-time, non-violent white-collar offense of this magnitude. Taking all these facts into account, a brief period of incarceration is warranted to serve as a deterrent and punishment for the breach of trust, but it should be relatively short to allow the defendant to return to the workforce and complete paying restitution. Therefore, I am sentencing the defendant to 12 months of incarceration.",
